    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uninitialized memory read in event processing\n\n### Summary\nThere is a read of uninitialized memory leading to undefined behavior downstream of function repack_event. The issue may be in repack_event or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/event.c`: Initialize event type in constructor functions\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/gui/event.c`: Remove redundant type assignment in send_event\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain timing conditions, the GUI event system may read uninitialized memory when processing REPACK events, causing unpredictable behavior including potential segfaults or incorrect widget repacking. This typically manifests as GUI rendering issues or crashes when widgets are dynamically updated.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Run the tracer GUI with multiple rapidly updating widgets\n2. Trigger frequent repack events through window resizing or widget modifications\n3. Observe intermittent crashes or rendering artifacts\n\nThe issue occurs because event objects were not fully initialized at creation time, creating a window where the type field could be read before being properly set.\n"
}